  <Docs>
    <summary>
      The <c>HTTPHeadersWriter</c> class facilitates the injection of trace propagation headers into network requests 
      targeted at a backend instrumented with Datadog and expecting <c>x-datadog-*</c> headers.
    </summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>Usage:</para>
      <code>
        var request = new HttpRequestMessage(...);

        var writer = new DDHTTPHeadersWriter();
        var span = DDTracer.Shared.StartSpan("network request");
        DDTracer.Shared.Inject(span.Context, OT.FormatTextMap, writer);

        foreach (var (field, value) in writer.TraceHeaderFields)
        {
            request.Headers.Add(field, value);
        }

        // call span.Finish() when the request completes
      </code>
    </remarks>
  </Docs>
